### Configure Playwright Web Server for Local Development

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-webserver-js.md

This configuration demonstrates how to set up Playwright's `webServer` to launch a local development server before tests. It specifies the command to start the server, the URL to wait for, and options to reuse an existing server or manage output.

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  // Run your local dev server before starting the tests
  webServer: {
    command: 'npm run start',
    url: 'http://localhost:3000',
    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,
    stdout: 'ignore',
    stderr: 'pipe',
  },
});
```

