### Capture Dynamic Port from Web Server Output in Playwright Config (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-api/class-testconfig.md

This Playwright configuration demonstrates using the `wait` property within `webServer` to capture a dynamically assigned port number. A regular expression extracts the port from the server's standard output, making it available as an environment variable for subsequent test runs.

```javascript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  webServer: {
    command: 'npm run start',
    wait: {
      stdout: '/Listening on port (?<my_server_port>\\d+)/'
    },
  },
});
```

