### Context Option - Proxy Configuration

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/params.md

Configure network proxy settings for a browser context. Supports HTTP and SOCKS proxies with optional authentication and domain bypass rules.

```APIDOC
## Proxy Configuration

### Description
Network proxy settings to use with this context. Defaults to none.

### Parameters

#### Proxy Object
- **server** (string) - Required - Proxy to be used for all requests. HTTP and SOCKS proxies are supported, for example `http://myproxy.com:3128` or `socks5://myproxy.com:3128`. Short form `myproxy.com:3128` is considered an HTTP proxy.
- **bypass** (string) - Optional - Comma-separated domains to bypass proxy, for example `".com, chromium.org, .domain.com"`.
- **username** (string) - Optional - Username to use if HTTP proxy requires authentication.
- **password** (string) - Optional - Password to use if HTTP proxy requires authentication.

### Request Example
```json
{
  "proxy": {
    "server": "http://myproxy.com:3128",
    "bypass": ".com, chromium.org, .domain.com",
    "username": "user",
    "password": "password"
  }
}
```
```

