### Configure Playwright Projects for Multiple Environments - TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-projects-js.md

Sets up Playwright projects to test against different environments (staging and production) with environment-specific configurations. Configures different baseURLs for each environment and applies different retry strategies: 2 retries for staging and 0 retries for production, with a shared 60-second timeout across all tests.

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  timeout: 60000, // Timeout is shared between all tests.
  projects: [
    {
      name: 'staging',
      use: {
        baseURL: 'staging.example.com',
      },
      retries: 2,
    },
    {
      name: 'production',
      use: {
        baseURL: 'production.example.com',
      },
      retries: 0,
    },
  ],
});
```
